The paper deals with the development of a computational model for predicting visual saliency in stereoscopic 3D videos. This involves the use of low-level and high-level cues, as well as the consideration of depth information. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of eye-tracking data and the evaluation of the proposed model's performance, which suggests the possibility of it being categorized under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The use of machine learning algorithms and the development of a new fovea-based model suggest the possibility of the paper being categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of stereoscopic 3D videos suggests the possibility of the paper being categorized under cs.GR (Graphics) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
